1
00:00:43,179 --> 00:00:45,520
There is a way out for us.

2
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,619
We can say...

3
00:00:50,090 --> 00:00:52,619
that Woo Il did it out of
excessive loyalty.

4
00:00:53,859 --> 00:00:56,329
- Father.
- He's already gone.

5
00:00:56,960 --> 00:01:00,030
We can say that we found out
and fired him in advance.

6
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,600
Please stop it!

7
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,840
Did you just yell at me?

8
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,670
Do you hear me now?

9
00:01:08,739 --> 00:01:10,640
You probably still don't hear me.

10
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:11,909
What?

11
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:15,109
Why do you want
only your voice heard?

12
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,450
You silence...

13
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,120
other people's voices or moans.
All you care about is...

14
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:23,489
if your voice is heard.

15
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,590
Do you think I do that
for my own sake?

16
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:27,560
It's all for your sake.

17
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:30,500
The world is full of noise.
Being so quiet,

18
00:01:30,530 --> 00:01:32,159
you can never survive.

19
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:34,170
I know that.

20
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:37,040
I know that too.

21
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:44,939
I've wondered what's wrong with me.

22
00:01:46,109 --> 00:01:48,209
I've always blamed myself.

23
00:01:49,849 --> 00:01:51,819
I've lived in shame.

24
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:55,549
What about you?

25
00:01:57,359 --> 00:02:00,590
How can you be so shameless?

26
00:02:28,889 --> 00:02:29,949
Hwan Gi.

27
00:02:30,490 --> 00:02:32,620
I talked to the press
on my way here.

28
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,060
I asked them to wait until
we announce our official position.

29
00:02:36,129 --> 00:02:39,000
Let's stop covering things up
or avoiding problems.

30
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,669
I'll take responsibility
and step down.

31
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:45,069
What?

32
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:46,909
To protect the company,
that's the best solution.

33
00:02:47,139 --> 00:02:48,610
Let me take responsibility.

34
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:51,710
I'm the one who's dealt with
all the shady things for Father.

35
00:02:51,740 --> 00:02:52,840
He's my father.

36
00:02:53,509 --> 00:02:54,509
Hwan Gi.

37
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:56,979
I asked you to come...

38
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,449
to hand over the company to you.

39
00:03:00,949 --> 00:03:02,650
Who am I to take over the company?

40
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,020
With what right?

41
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:21,569
I trust you.

42
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:24,210
You're the only one
who can save the company.

43
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:58,479
You fool.

44
00:04:42,889 --> 00:04:43,920
Go.

45
00:04:46,589 --> 00:04:48,230
Where would I go?

46
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:51,259
I put away the pictures
of your mom and sister...

47
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,529
because I wanted you to forget about
everything and go your own way.

48
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,399
How would I forget about everything?

49
00:04:58,439 --> 00:05:00,139
Ji Hye and Ro Woon.

50
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:03,310
Even our names are inseparable.

51
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,740
Is that what you've been thinking?

52
00:05:07,649 --> 00:05:09,680
I named you Ro Woon...

53
00:05:10,149 --> 00:05:13,050
hoping you'd live
an interesting life.

54
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,189
It's not meant to be
put together with "Ji Hye"...

55
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:18,220
and mean "wise".

56
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,660
Don't get stuck like I did.

57
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:25,100
Go out to the wide world.

58
00:05:25,459 --> 00:05:28,230
Live with people who recognize
your worth.

59
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:30,199
Dad.

60
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:33,569
Leave with a smile, not tears.

61
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:36,209
You look ugly when you cry.

62
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:40,110
You might be sent back.

63
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:37,769
Silent Monster...

64
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,370
- Look to the front.
- Right.

65
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:48,209
- Here we go.
- Be careful.

66
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:51,279
- A little more.
- Lift it.

67
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:52,910
Hang in there.

68
00:07:55,649 --> 00:07:57,480
Boss must be angry.

69
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,350
Are you okay?

70
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,620
Boss, did you collapse?

71
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:09,259
You're up.

72
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:11,500
We've decided on what to call you.

73
00:08:11,529 --> 00:08:12,529
Sorry?

74
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:15,600
We're all going to call you Boss.

75
00:08:47,429 --> 00:08:49,669
Why do you have to resign?

76
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:52,940
Leaving doesn't mean
you're taking responsibility.

77
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:56,309
I'm sorry I couldn't
stay with you...

78
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:58,980
until the end.

79
00:09:01,809 --> 00:09:03,049
Thanks to you all,

80
00:09:04,149 --> 00:09:05,480
I could change.

81
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:08,450
We're the ones who have changed.

82
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:11,620
You helped us all grow.

83
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,659
After you leave us,

84
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:17,230
who will trust us like you did?

85
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,929
Please don't go.

86
00:09:21,299 --> 00:09:23,299
Why would you make
a woman cry?

87
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:25,740
Please don't do this.

88
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,309
I don't want to become sentimental.

89
00:09:28,340 --> 00:09:29,639
Even Sun Bong is crying.

90
00:09:31,309 --> 00:09:32,909
I've been trying so hard not to.

91
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,480
It's the red light.

92
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:43,450
Don't say anything.

93
00:09:44,019 --> 00:09:45,919
The red light is on. All right?

94
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:47,629
Here.

95
00:09:54,970 --> 00:09:56,100
Please don't go.

96
00:09:57,129 --> 00:09:58,269
Please don't leave.

97
00:10:11,649 --> 00:10:13,019
Not because you're Eun Yi Soo.

98
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:15,519
Because it's you.

99
00:10:59,429 --> 00:11:01,529
Excuse me. Please get off.

100
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:09,539
You better not run away
again this time.

101
00:11:16,649 --> 00:11:17,980
Are you not going to get off?

102
00:11:39,769 --> 00:11:41,970
It looks like it's 100 percent
your fault once again.

103
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:46,139
How can you drive without even
glancing at what's behind you?

104
00:11:48,779 --> 00:11:51,019
No matter how hard I try
to keep a safe distance from you...

105
00:11:55,519 --> 00:11:56,620
I just...

106
00:11:58,019 --> 00:12:00,159
can't keep myself away from you.

107
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:49,000
He became alone again.

108
00:14:09,019 --> 00:14:10,649
Why are you out here alone again?

109
00:14:14,490 --> 00:14:15,590
The red light?

110
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:17,659
The green light.

111
00:14:18,830 --> 00:14:20,429
Then why didn't you wake me up?

112
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,070
Let me tag along, will you?

113
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,970
Don't kick me
when I'm trying to wake you up.

114
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:28,470
Did I do that?

115
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:41,090
He was alone
even when we were together.

116
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:49,259
(Episode 16: It's Okay to Be Shy)

117
00:14:49,629 --> 00:14:51,860
Boss! Boss, Boss!

118
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:54,769
Boss! Boss!

119
00:14:55,169 --> 00:14:57,399
Boss, Boss, Boss.

120
00:14:58,340 --> 00:15:00,940
Boss, we have a big problem.
Come out.

121
00:15:01,169 --> 00:15:03,570
Boss, hurry up. Hurry.

122
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:04,940
We have a huge problem.

123
00:15:05,409 --> 00:15:07,240
What's wrong? What happened?

124
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:11,379
- I'm bored.
- What?

125
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,519
You got me worried. Goodness.

126
00:15:15,149 --> 00:15:17,860
To me, it's a really big problem.

127
00:15:17,889 --> 00:15:20,419
I might actually die of boredom.

128
00:15:20,659 --> 00:15:23,460
You've been stuck in this room.
Do you know how many days it's been?

129
00:15:24,299 --> 00:15:25,629
I came here to be bored.

130
00:15:26,299 --> 00:15:28,929
Right, but until when
are you going to keep this up?

131
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,179
Okay, fine.

132
00:15:38,210 --> 00:15:40,710
I'll be bored out of my mind.

133
00:16:02,129 --> 00:16:03,870
How can she eat chips in bed?

134
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,500
From sweet and salty
to spicy flavors,

135
00:16:06,539 --> 00:16:08,870
she even got all sorts of flavors
that compliment each other.

136
00:16:09,509 --> 00:16:11,279
She hasn't even showered yet.

137
00:16:11,309 --> 00:16:14,450
Plus, how can she be rolling in bed
in her outside clothes?

138
00:16:15,210 --> 00:16:16,350
Shall I tell her?

139
00:16:17,549 --> 00:16:21,490
No, I can't let such trivial matters
ruin our happy moments.

140
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:24,720
But I have to sleep
in that bed tonight.

141
00:16:25,559 --> 00:16:27,690
The dust from outside, chip crumbs,

142
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:30,360
and dust mites will be having
a party on that very bed.

143
00:16:30,659 --> 00:16:31,799
What should I do?

144
00:16:32,129 --> 00:16:35,299
The second I tell her to go wash up,
she'll probably...

145
00:16:35,669 --> 00:16:38,399
Should I take a shower? Then...

146
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:42,039
From head to toe?

147
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,279
(Decollete)

148
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:50,649
Yes, she's certainly capable
of doing it.

149
00:16:50,879 --> 00:16:52,779
She'll assume
I'm having dirty thoughts.

150
00:16:55,289 --> 00:16:58,019
What's up? Is there something
you want to tell me?

151
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:02,860
Yes, I should lure her elsewhere.

152
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,099
While she's doing something else,

153
00:17:05,130 --> 00:17:07,230
I'll shake off the blanket.

154
00:17:09,569 --> 00:17:10,970
You should step out.

155
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:13,039
It's gotten a lot warmer.

156
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:16,109
Really?

157
00:17:18,509 --> 00:17:20,640
I don't want to. I want to stay
in bed for a bit more.

158
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:24,309
You said you're bored.

159
00:17:24,349 --> 00:17:26,420
You told me to stay bored.

160
00:17:26,450 --> 00:17:28,549
I'm so bored now. It's perfect.

161
00:17:32,890 --> 00:17:33,990
That failed.

162
00:17:41,299 --> 00:17:44,230
Do you want to play this with me?

163
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,440
The loser will grant the winner's
wish. What do you say?

164
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:06,460
Yes. Your turn.

165
00:18:06,490 --> 00:18:07,559
Goodness.

166
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,660
Gosh, seriously.

167
00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:16,329
Goodness.

168
00:18:18,970 --> 00:18:20,740
That's foul play.

169
00:18:23,509 --> 00:18:25,039
Hurry up. We don't have time.

170
00:18:39,890 --> 00:18:40,960
Yes.

171
00:18:41,859 --> 00:18:44,130
Why are you getting so competitive?

172
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,730
Hurry up. Come on!

173
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,059
Don't!

174
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,400
It'll fall. It's falling.

175
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:57,539
Yes, yes! Yes!

176
00:19:00,210 --> 00:19:01,880
Are you that happy you won?

177
00:19:01,910 --> 00:19:04,309
Yes, I'm happy. I'm thrilled.

178
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,579
All right. What's your wish?

179
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,230
Stay still.

180
00:19:24,569 --> 00:19:26,569
There. It's done.

181
00:19:26,839 --> 00:19:28,009
Just a second.

182
00:19:29,170 --> 00:19:30,869
Hang on. 1, 2.

183
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:36,779
Let's see.

184
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,519
Okay.

185
00:19:42,589 --> 00:19:44,289
You better not post it anywhere.

186
00:19:44,619 --> 00:19:47,420
No way. I got my wish.

187
00:19:49,089 --> 00:19:50,390
You can wash up now.

188
00:19:50,430 --> 00:19:53,759
My eyes are... Look at my lips.

189
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:56,500
Good. That was natural.

190
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:58,539
Go wash up.

191
00:19:59,769 --> 00:20:03,009
I kind of like it now.

192
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:06,279
You're good at doing makeup.

193
00:20:08,380 --> 00:20:09,950
I'll just sleep like this today.

194
00:20:11,009 --> 00:20:12,579
- Just like that?
- Yes.

195
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:16,549
You can't. It'll ruin your skin.

196
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,220
Go wash up. You'll ruin your skin.

197
00:20:18,259 --> 00:20:20,220
It's okay to skip a night. Anyway,

198
00:20:20,559 --> 00:20:23,390
we have to go for another round.
I'll pay you back.

199
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:24,529
Go.

200
00:20:55,029 --> 00:20:57,059
My wish is...

201
00:20:57,829 --> 00:21:00,460
for us to just sleep as we are now.

202
00:21:00,730 --> 00:21:05,099
Then tomorrow, we have to go out
as soon as we wake up.

203
00:21:17,309 --> 00:21:20,650
Someplace where you can hear
the echo

204
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:24,119
Let's look for the fall
in the valley

205
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:28,660
Let us go on a trip

206
00:21:30,259 --> 00:21:32,500
This is so much fun.

207
00:21:36,329 --> 00:21:39,269
Am I too excited? I'm so hungry.

208
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:42,809
I better have some snack.

209
00:21:42,839 --> 00:21:43,910
Again?

210
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:46,740
Should I have some chips?

211
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:50,180
My goodness.

212
00:21:52,319 --> 00:21:53,349
Gosh.

213
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:04,829
What a waste.

214
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:09,069
What a waste.

215
00:22:10,670 --> 00:22:12,369
I dropped all of them.

216
00:22:15,069 --> 00:22:17,210
This is too much.

217
00:22:17,869 --> 00:22:19,609
It's not her bed to sleep alone.

218
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:23,480
She made our bed a club
for ticks and dust.

219
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:25,319
And now, my car too?

220
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:28,190
Does she not know
what cars mean to men?

221
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:31,660
Should I tell her
she can't eat in here?

222
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:34,359
I'd look too narrow-minded.

223
00:22:34,789 --> 00:22:37,289
Also, she's so excited today.

224
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:38,529
Do you want one?

225
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:40,859
I'm okay.

226
00:22:43,630 --> 00:22:45,539
Is this a red light?

227
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:47,140
No.

228
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:51,480
Come on. Just tell me.

229
00:22:51,609 --> 00:22:54,079
You have to tell me for me to know.

230
00:22:59,150 --> 00:23:00,650
This won't do.

231
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:04,420
A chip will help. Here.

232
00:23:04,519 --> 00:23:05,859
Open up.

233
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,289
No. I'm driving.

234
00:23:09,329 --> 00:23:10,630
This is dangerous.

235
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:13,130
Eating home food all the
time is boring.

236
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,900
You need to eat snacks
once in a while.

237
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:16,630
See?

238
00:23:17,829 --> 00:23:22,210
When you eat chips,
it gets rid of your stress.

239
00:23:22,910 --> 00:23:23,940
Here.

240
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:27,779
I'll pick you a chip
that looks delicious. Here.

241
00:23:28,039 --> 00:23:29,650
- No.
- Come on.

242
00:23:31,049 --> 00:23:34,250
Here, open up. Good. Chew.

243
00:23:34,279 --> 00:23:36,289
- I'm driving, be careful.
- Last one.

244
00:23:37,819 --> 00:23:40,289
- It's okay, I don't want it.
- Last one.

245
00:23:43,660 --> 00:23:45,660
Isn't it good? Do you want another?

246
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,759
No, I don't want it. Stop.

247
00:23:47,799 --> 00:23:49,130
- A big one?
- I don't want it.

248
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:50,900
Last one.

249
00:23:52,069 --> 00:23:54,140
Wait. Hold on.

250
00:24:13,789 --> 00:24:17,430
Boss,
are you going to talk it out now?

251
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,359
Good thinking.

252
00:24:24,670 --> 00:24:27,400
- Can I really be honest?
- Of course. Go ahead.

253
00:24:27,599 --> 00:24:30,269
Don't distract me when I'm driving.

254
00:24:30,410 --> 00:24:31,839
I can't focus.

255
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,640
It's dangerous
even for good drivers.

256
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:37,849
- Safety comes first on the road.
- Okay.

257
00:24:38,579 --> 00:24:40,750
I was distracting, right?

258
00:24:40,779 --> 00:24:41,849
Also...

259
00:24:43,349 --> 00:24:46,089
I don't like it
when people eat in my car.

260
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:49,390
You wouldn't go in bed
with those greasy hands, would you?

261
00:24:50,759 --> 00:24:53,099
Please wash up before bed.

262
00:24:53,329 --> 00:24:56,299
If you don't ever shower,
you'll get sick.

263
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:57,930
It's disgusting.

264
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:02,140
What? Is there more?

265
00:25:03,369 --> 00:25:06,140
Television. Yes.
When we're watching television,

266
00:25:06,210 --> 00:25:07,740
please focus.

267
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:11,880
Why do you keep asking me
after not paying attention?

268
00:25:11,980 --> 00:25:13,750
Don't watch it, or don't ask me.

269
00:25:13,779 --> 00:25:15,420
At the least, don't be curious.

270
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:17,490
That feels good. Are there more?

